    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-01-30T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-01-30T10:00:00-05:00" n="207"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d207">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/2366</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-30T16:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 30, 1916, 4 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received January 31, 11.10 a. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3409. Forgot to state in my 3406 yesterday that <persName corresp="#p_ZAFM1"
                        >Zimmermann</persName> also said that there was no longer any international
                    law, and that anyway the coming of the submarine has made a change in
                    international law necessary. I said that it was statements of that kind which
                    made all other nations fear Germany; that as far as we were concerned Germany
                    could not change the rules of international law during this war without our
                    consent and merely to suit Germany’s needs or convenience. He said that
                        <persName corresp="#p_BJHACV1">Bernstorff</persName>’s proposed note made
                    Germany give up submarine war. I said: “Not at all. You can continue to use
                    submarines, but in notes already sent by you you have agreed to put passengers
                    and crew in safety and not to sink merchant ships without warning.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gerard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
